Overview
ProjectCompass is an open‑source clarity and rhythm framework built from directions, geometry, lunar cycles, and mythic timing.
It teaches people how to live inside coherent rhythms — daily, weekly, monthly, seasonal, and lunar — using gentle‑adult explanations, mythic structure, and accessible timing tools.

This repository contains:

the ProjectCompass Wiki (Levels 1–3)

the Medium Series archive

lunar resources

diagrams, charts, and timing wheels

Kids Compass + Audio Series scaffolding

open‑source educational materials

Everything here is designed to be simple, structured, and sustainable.

Levels
ProjectCompass is organized into three learning layers:

Level 1 — First Level
Beginner rhythm literacy:

shapes (line, circle, spiral)

daily/weekly/monthly rhythms

simple lunar timing

foundational timing questions

Wiki: /wiki/1-first-level.md

Level 2 — Medium Level
Gentle‑adult learning:

Hero + Feminine mythic timing

lunar cycles

4‑week lunar ritual

global lunar trackers

Medium article scaffolding

Wiki: /wiki/2-medium-level.md

Level 3 — Friday Level
Advanced rhythm literacy:

12‑sign rhythm grid

Hero/Feminine seasons by sign

personal lunar timing map

deeper mythic synthesis

Wiki: /wiki/3-friday-signs.md

Medium Series
The ProjectCompass Medium Series explores mythic timing, lunar rhythm, creative coherence, and gentle‑adult learning.

Articles are published weekly and archived here.

Series link: (add your Medium link here)

Publishing rhythm:

July: 2 posts/week

August: 3 posts/week

September: 4 posts/week (if comfortable)

Lunar Resources (Real‑Time Tracking)
ProjectCompass uses world‑class lunar data sources:

NASA — Moon Phase & Libration  
https://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov/5048 (svs.gsfc.nasa.gov in Bing)

TheSkyLive (EU)  
https://theskylive.com/moon-info

TimeAndDate (Global)  
https://www.timeanddate.com/moon/

ESA — Lunar Science  
https://www.esa.int/Science_Exploration/Human_and_Robotic_Exploration/Moon (esa.int in Bing)

These tools support timing literacy and lunar‑based rhythm planning.

